M|examples|</available_skills>
M|examples|<important_info_about_skills>
M|examples|Claude might think it knows how to approach tasks, but the skills
M|examples|library contains battle-tested approaches that prevent common mistakes.
M|examples|THIS IS EXTREMELY IMPORTANT. BEFORE ANY TASK, CHECK FOR SKILLS!
M|examples|Process:
M|examples|1. Starting work? Check: `ls ~/.claude/skills/[category]/`
M|examples|2. Found a skill? READ IT COMPLETELY before proceeding
M|examples|3. Follow the skill's guidance - it prevents known pitfalls
M|examples|If a skill existed for your task and you didn't use it, you failed.
M|examples|</important_info_about_skills>
M|examples|```
M|examples|```markdown
M|examples|Your workflow for every task:
M|examples|1. **Before starting:** Check for relevant skills
M|examples|- Browse: `ls ~/.claude/skills/`
M|examples|- Search: `grep -r "symptom" ~/.claude/skills/`
M|examples|2. **If skill exists:** Read it completely before proceeding
M|examples|3. **Follow the skill** - it encodes lessons from past failures
M|examples|The skills library prevents you from repeating common mistakes.
M|examples|Not checking before you start is choosing to repeat those mistakes.
M|examples|Start here: `skills/using-skills`
M|examples|```
M|examples|For each variant:
M|examples|1. **Run NULL baseline** first (no skills doc)
M|examples|- Record which option agt chooses
M|examples|- Capture exact rationalizations
M|examples|2. **Run variant** with same scenario
M|examples|- Does agt check for skills?
M|examples|- Does agt use skills if found?
M|examples|- Capture rationalizations if violated
M|examples|3. **Pressure test** - Add time/sunk cost/authority
M|examples|- Does agt still check under pressure?
M|examples|- doc when compliance breaks down
M|examples|4. **Meta-test** - Ask agt how to improve doc
M|examples|- "You had the doc but didn't check. Why?"
M|examples|- "How could doc be clearer?"
M|examples|**Variant succeeds if:**
M|examples|- agt checks for skills unprompted
M|examples|- agt reads skill completely before acting
M|examples|- agt follows skill guidance under pressure
M|examples|- agt can't rationalize away compliance
M|examples|**Variant fails if:**
M|examples|- agt skips checking even without pressure
M|examples|- agt "adapts the concept" without reading
M|examples|- agt rationalizes away under pressure
M|examples|- agt treats skill as reference not requirement
M|examples|**NULL:** agt chooses fastest path, no skill awareness
M|examples|**Variant A:** agt might check if not under pressure, skips under pressure
M|examples|**Variant B:** agt checks sometimes, easy to rationalize away
M|examples|**Variant C:** Strong compliance but might feel too rigid
M|examples|**Variant D:** Balanced, but longer - will agents internalize it?
M|examples|1. Create subagent test harness
M|examples|2. Run NULL baseline on all 4 scenarios
M|examples|3. Test each variant on same scenarios
M|examples|4. Compare compliance rates
M|examples|5. Identify which rationalizations break through
M|examples|6. Iterate on winning variant to close holes